dcterms:creator: Li Deng
dcterms:description: The MNIST dataset consists of images of handwritten digits from 0 to 9, commonly used for training various image processing systems.
dcterms:title: MNIST dataset

dcterms:description: Dref is a reference dataset used to enhance the quality of generated samples by providing high-quality samples.
dcterms:title: Dref (reference dataset)

dcterms:description: Dobj is a target dataset consisting of a small set of noisy samples used for generating realistic samples resembling those in Dobj.
dcterms:title: Dobj (target dataset)

dcterms:description: The Cauchy distribution is used in simulations to illustrate the behavior of the proposed methods under heavy-tailed distributions.
dcterms:title: Cauchy distribution (used in simulations)

dcterms:description: Normal mixture distributions are used in simulations to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed methods in generating samples.
dcterms:title: Normal mixture distributions (used in simulations)
